\fs32 \cf0 \cb6 for chapter 1 tell me which csv styles/sections are used where. write it in sequence in chat. for text not in the csv sections , write it, like: "What if the difficulty you're facing isn't punishment for doing something wrong, but life inviting you to discover how much you can actually hold?\
\
Today we explore what it means to give yourself complete permission to be exactly where you are. Burnout is something many people experience. You'll learn that the impulse to judge your current experience is often more painful than the experience itself. You know what it's like when Burnout hits you\'97how it disrupts your workflow, keeps you up scrolling at 2am, how your mind loops on the same anxieties. In this opening chapter, you'll practice seeing your current challenges through the lens of wisdom rather than criticism, understanding rather than judgment. Imagine waking up and feeling genuinely rested.\
\
I struggled with Burnout for longer than I want to admit. For a while, I treated it like a personal flaw\'97like my nervous system was a design defect. It showed up in small moments first: a tight chest, a racing mind, the urge to sprint ahead of my own day. I kept trying to solve it with willpower. I could muscle through a lot\'97but I couldn\'92t muscle through my body. Eventually I realized the first step wasn\'92t fixing. It was noticing\'97without turning every sensation into a story about who I was.\
\
The shift didn\'92t come from a single hack. It came from understanding what my nervous system was trying to do\'97and why it kept choosing the same alarm. I started to see Burnout as information, not an identity. Once that clicked, I stopped treating the sensation like an enemy and started treating it like a signal. That gave me a small pocket of choice\'97just enough to do one thing differently in the moment.\
\
