\cf0 Breathwalk (Movement + Breath)\'97a Kundalini yoga practice popularized by Yogi Bhajan. This combines movement with breathwork to create a meditative, energizing experience. You'll inhale for 4 steps and exhale for 4 steps, synchronizing breath with movement. Stand tall. Feel your feet on the ground. You'll walk at a natural pace while breathing in rhythm with your steps. You'll hear tones that match your walking rhythm\'97one tone for each breath cycle as you walk. The sound flows with your steps and breath: in-in-in-in as you walk, out-out-out-out as you walk. The tone keeps your rhythm steady. If you need to adjust the breath-to-step ratio, do so. The goal is rhythm, not strain. There's no failing this. Follow the tones. Trust your breath. Now I'm going to step back. It's just you and the tones. We begin.\
Inhale for four steps: in, two, three, four.\uc0\u8232 Exhale for four steps: out, two, three, four.\
Let your breath and movement become one. Nice.\
Now just relax and breathe normally. How does your body feel after moving with your breath? More present? More alive around Burnout?\
